Operators, who argue that thrilling rides have been pivotal to the Luna Park experience since the 1980's, are currently seeking planning approval for the ride.

In an application, they have claimed the ride did not have any 'significant adverse impacts' and was helping the park remain in operation.

Hair Raiser allows patrons to be elevated to the top of the tower, witnessing sweeping views of the harbour, before plunging at more than 80km/h.

It was revealed last year that the operators never obtained the required approvals to erect the ride.

North Sydney Council have claimed the ride is 'visually offensive' and unsuitable for its location.

