A number of scathing submissions to the council have been made by locals. In one, the neighbour writes:

'We object to this ride as it is operating without DA approval. We object to its position and the flashing lights which can operate 24 hours a day as this causes noise pollution and loss of amenity to adjacent residents.'

Another wrote it was 'an ugly monstrosity' akin to a permanent crane on the skyline.

Luna Park was forced to close in 1996 due to financial burdens, including the closure of some rides due to noise complaints. It was reopened in 2004.

It is now on the state heritage register. 

 

